description:
&lt;p&gt;NMC Registered Band 5 Nurses required to work at North Bristol Trust, one of the UK’s largest NHS Hospital Trusts, based at Southmead Hospital, North Bristol&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why apply? &lt;/strong&gt;Our staff nurse roles offer a fantastic opportunity to take a role with-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cutting-edge clinical practice- &lt;/strong&gt;Southmead Hospital is a centre of excellent in a range of services and major specialities. Our pioneering treatments and advances in care have won international recognition, placing us at the forefront of medical knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Career development&lt;/strong&gt;- our well-structured and supported preceptorship programme will support you to achieve your career aspirations and realise your full potential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An excellent location&lt;/strong&gt;- the Trust resides within one of the most vibrant cities in the UK, Bristol. Voted the best city to live in 2017, the city is famous for its year round festivals, award-winning cycle tracks, exceptional gastronomy, stunning cityscapes and awe-inspiring street art.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role- &lt;/strong&gt;As a Staff Nurse, you will play a key role within a team of nursing staff, in the delivery of high quality, evidence based patient-centred care. We currently have roles available in a variety of specialities, including-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medicine- Emergency, Complex and Specialist Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Theatres – Scrubs &amp; Medirooms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Neonatal Intensive Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Surgical Wards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Musculoskeletal and Neurosciences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Renal Wards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intensive Care Unit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to work flexibly across all of our shift patterns is vital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Please note, we are unable to accept applications from candidates who do not have registration with the Nursing and Midwifery Council for this role**&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information on &lt;strong&gt;North Bristol Trust Careers&lt;/strong&gt;. Follow us on Facebook, Twitter and LinkedIn See our Nursing Career Video&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
